1455
02:22:21,651 --> 02:22:25,860
"I wish I could've taken you
to your first day of school."

1456
02:22:29,360 --> 02:22:31,235
Six:

1457
02:22:32,068 --> 02:22:36,452
"I wish I could've been there
to teach you to play the piano."

1458
02:22:38,735 --> 02:22:41,610
1981, I was thirteen:

1459
02:22:41,818 --> 02:22:46,026
"I wish I could've told you
not to chase some boy."

1460
02:22:46,318 --> 02:22:50,818
"I wish I could've held you
when you had a broken heart."

1461
02:22:51,401 --> 02:22:54,818
"I wish I could've
been your father."

1462
02:22:55,027 --> 02:22:58,735
"Nothing I ever did
will replace that."

1463
02:23:04,818 --> 02:23:07,318
I guess he went to India.

1464
02:23:07,495 --> 02:23:10,702
For what it's worth,
it's never to late,

1465
02:23:10,903 --> 02:23:15,318
or in my case, too early,
to be whoever you want to be.

1466
02:23:19,027 --> 02:23:23,455
There is no time limit,
start whenever you want.

1467
02:23:24,693 --> 02:23:30,276
You can change or stay the same.
There are no rules to this thing.

1468
02:23:31,735 --> 02:23:35,151
We can make the best
or the worst of it.

1469
02:23:35,329 --> 02:23:38,235
I hope you make the best of it.

1470
02:23:40,735 --> 02:23:44,985
And I hope you see
things that startle you.

1471
02:23:45,693 --> 02:23:50,151
I hope you feel things
you never felt before.

1472
02:23:51,663 --> 02:23:55,901
I hope you meet people with
a different point of view.

1473
02:23:56,280 --> 02:23:59,985
I hope you live a life
you're proud of.

1474
02:24:01,860 --> 02:24:04,743
If you find that you're not,

1475
02:24:05,026 --> 02:24:10,077
I hope you have the strength
to start all over again.

1476
02:24:12,454 --> 02:24:15,776
He had been gone a long time.

1477
02:24:17,318 --> 02:24:20,235
I'll see you next thursday.

1478
02:24:22,402 --> 02:24:26,068
-Good night, miss Daisy.
-Good night, sweetheart.

1479
02:24:43,568 --> 02:24:46,651
I'm sorry, we're closing.

1480
02:24:48,443 --> 02:24:51,026
Can I help you?

1481
02:24:51,652 --> 02:24:55,110
Are you here to
pick somebody up?

1482
02:25:04,485 --> 02:25:07,360
Why did you come back?

1483
02:25:07,735 --> 02:25:09,360
Mom?

1484
02:25:10,151 --> 02:25:11,818
Mom!

1485
02:25:12,485 --> 02:25:14,818
You ready yet?

1486
02:25:16,985 --> 02:25:18,651
Mom, what's wrong?

1487
02:25:18,740 --> 02:25:22,151
I was just hearing a very sad
story about a mutual friend,

1488
02:25:22,236 --> 02:25:25,402
who I hadn't seen
for a very long time.

1489
02:25:25,610 --> 02:25:28,610
Caroline, this is Benjamin.

1490
02:25:28,818 --> 02:25:32,818
You knew him when
you were just a baby.

1491
02:25:33,401 --> 02:25:35,571
Hi. -Hi.

1492
02:25:37,193 --> 02:25:38,777
Hey!

1493
02:25:40,951 --> 02:25:43,526
I'm sorry, I thought
you were done.

1494
02:25:43,735 --> 02:25:47,659
Oh, this is a friend of my
family's, Benjamin Button.

1495
02:25:47,860 --> 02:25:52,028
This is my husband, Robert.
-How do you do.

1496
02:25:52,529 --> 02:25:54,610
Pleasure.

1497
02:26:01,610 --> 02:26:05,610
It was very nice to meet you.
We'll be in the car, darling.

1498
02:26:05,785 --> 02:26:07,901
Alright. -Bye.

1499
02:26:08,610 --> 02:26:11,026
I'm just locking up.

1500
02:26:18,574 --> 02:26:22,163
She's beautiful,
like her mother.

1501
02:26:22,777 --> 02:26:25,443
Does she dance?
-Not very well.

1502
02:26:25,527 --> 02:26:28,286
I guess that'd be from
my side of things.

1503
02:26:28,487 --> 02:26:30,901
She's a dear sweet girl.

1504
02:26:31,110 --> 02:26:35,193
She seems a little lost.
But then, who isn't at twelve?

1505
02:26:35,492 --> 02:26:39,568
There's a lot of her
that reminds me of you.

1506
02:26:40,318 --> 02:26:44,153
My husband, he's a widower
... was a widower.

1507
02:26:44,745 --> 02:26:48,985
He's an incredibly kind,
bright, adventurous man.

1508
02:26:51,744 --> 02:26:55,318
He's been a terrific father.
-Good.

1509
02:26:59,193 --> 02:27:03,443
You're so much younger.
-Only on the outside.

1510
02:27:05,198 --> 02:27:07,526
You were right.

1511
02:27:08,528 --> 02:27:11,985
I couldn't have been
raising both of you.

1512
02:27:12,193 --> 02:27:14,651
I'm not that strong.

1513
02:27:17,985 --> 02:27:20,860
So, where are you staying?

1514
02:27:22,193 --> 02:27:24,193
What are you gonna do?

1515
02:27:24,277 --> 02:27:27,943
I'm staying at the Pontchartrain
hotel on the avenue.

1516
02:27:28,151 --> 02:27:31,151
I don't know what I'm gonna do.

1517
02:27:38,994 --> 02:27:41,527
They're waiting.

1518
02:28:22,742 --> 02:28:26,370
I remember that.
That was him.

1519
02:28:28,235 --> 02:28:30,693
Hurricane's changed direction.
It's gonna make a landfall

1520
02:28:30,779 --> 02:28:32,779
some time soon. -Am I
supposed to do something?

1521
02:28:32,901 --> 02:28:34,985
Arrangements are being made to
move people, but it's up to you.

1522
02:28:35,110 --> 02:28:37,068
No, no, we're staying.

1523
02:28:37,276 --> 02:28:40,276
I'll let you know
if anything changes.

1524
02:28:41,776 --> 02:28:44,818
That night, while I was
sitting and wandering

1525
02:28:45,026 --> 02:28:49,068
why I came back at all,
there was a knock at the door.

1526
02:28:52,068 --> 02:28:54,152
Come in.

1527
02:29:07,777 --> 02:29:10,529
Are you alright?

1528
02:29:12,527 --> 02:29:16,776
I'm sorry, I don't know
what am I doing here.

1529
02:29:25,568 --> 02:29:28,068
Nothing lasts.

1530
02:29:30,827 --> 02:29:33,901
I never stopped loving you.

1531
02:29:39,193 --> 02:29:42,235
Benjamin, I'm an old woman now.

1532
02:29:52,235 --> 02:29:55,526
Some things you never forget.

1533
02:30:43,068 --> 02:30:45,318
Goodnight, Benjamin.

1534
02:30:46,287 --> 02:30:48,497
Goodnight, Daisy.

1535
02:30:51,318 --> 02:30:53,996
And as I knew I would...

1536
02:30:54,198 --> 02:30:56,652
I watched her go.

1537
02:30:58,193 --> 02:31:01,235
That's the last thing he wrote.

1538
02:31:01,824 --> 02:31:06,735
Some time after
your father passed,

1539
02:31:07,491 --> 02:31:10,360
there was a call.

1540
02:31:12,235 --> 02:31:15,693
Hello? Yes, speaking.

1541
02:31:19,443 --> 02:31:22,526
I'm sorry, I don't understand.

1542
02:31:31,443 --> 02:31:34,276
It's the corner house.

1543
02:31:55,776 --> 02:31:57,985
Come on in!

1544
02:32:02,658 --> 02:32:04,787
I'm Daisy Fuller.
-I'm David Hernandez

1545
02:32:04,988 --> 02:32:08,610
with the Orleans Parish dept
of Child Welfare Services.

1546
02:32:08,818 --> 02:32:12,068
He was living in the
condemned building.

1547
02:32:12,985 --> 02:32:16,243
The police found this
with him, this address,

1548
02:32:16,443 --> 02:32:19,235
it's got your name
in here a lot.

1549
02:32:19,568 --> 02:32:22,401
He's in a very poor health.
He was taken to the hospital.

1550
02:32:22,580 --> 02:32:26,456
He doesn't seem to know who or
where he is. He's very confused.

1551
02:32:26,658 --> 02:32:30,318
I was telling Mr Hernandez
that Benjamin is one of us.

1552
02:32:30,495 --> 02:32:34,568
If he needs a place to stay,
it's alright. He can stay here.

1553
02:33:03,276 --> 02:33:05,071
Benjamin.

1554
02:33:08,401 --> 02:33:11,068
You play beautifully.

1555
02:33:13,735 --> 02:33:15,818
He doesn't seem to
like to be touched.

1556
02:33:15,910 --> 02:33:17,985
He goes in and out of
states of recognition.

1557
02:33:18,068 --> 02:33:20,276
The doctors said if they
didn't know any better...

1558
02:33:20,360 --> 02:33:22,951
it is the beginnings
of dementia.

1559
02:33:23,451 --> 02:33:26,236
Do you remember me?

1560
02:33:28,443 --> 02:33:30,652
I'm Daisy.

1561
02:33:32,238 --> 02:33:34,581
I'm Benjamin.

1562
02:33:39,610 --> 02:33:42,735
It's nice to meet you, Benjamin.

1563
02:33:44,235 --> 02:33:49,493
Do you mind if I sit with you?
I would love to hear you play.

1564
02:33:53,318 --> 02:33:55,868
Do I know you?

1565
02:34:00,193 --> 02:34:05,777
And every day I would stop by
to make sure he was comfortable.

1566
02:34:07,985 --> 02:34:10,651
Don't think that I don't
know what you're doing!

1567
02:34:10,829 --> 02:34:13,193
You're all fucking liars!

1568
02:34:13,526 --> 02:34:17,320
He doesn't believe
he just had his breakfast.

1569
02:34:19,532 --> 02:34:24,943
Why don't we see if we can find
something else for you to do.

1570
02:34:25,151 --> 02:34:28,568
I have a feeling there's a lot
of things I can't remember.

1571
02:34:28,776 --> 02:34:31,235
Like what, sugar?

1572
02:34:31,943 --> 02:34:36,032
It's like...
there's this whole life I had,

1573
02:34:36,860 --> 02:34:40,068
and I can't remember what it was.

1574
02:34:42,235 --> 02:34:46,902
It's okay.
It's okay to forget things.

1575
02:34:47,318 --> 02:34:52,610
Many times he would simply
forget who or where he was.

1576
02:34:54,652 --> 02:34:57,276
It wasn't easy.
-Benjamin!

1577
02:34:57,485 --> 02:34:59,943
I can see everything!
I can see the big river!

1578
02:35:00,151 --> 02:35:02,610
That's right. You can see
everything, sweetheart.

1579
02:35:02,818 --> 02:35:06,026
I can see the graveyard where
mama's buried and other people.

1580
02:35:06,235 --> 02:35:09,943
I want you to come down!
-What if I can fly?

1581
02:35:10,151 --> 02:35:13,112
I knew a man who could fly.

1582
02:35:13,318 --> 02:35:16,776
Come down and I'll
tell you all about him.

1583
02:35:19,568 --> 02:35:22,328
Somebody go up there.

1584
02:35:27,699 --> 02:35:30,776
He was five when I moved in.

1585
02:35:30,985 --> 02:35:35,331
Nearly the same age I was
when I had met him.

1586
02:35:41,576 --> 02:35:47,401
This is the picture of Old Man
Kangaroo at 5 in the afternoon,

1587
02:35:48,027 --> 02:35:51,901
when he got his
beautiful hind legs.

1588
02:35:52,693 --> 02:35:58,360
The days passed, and I watched
as he forgot how to walk...

1589
02:36:03,527 --> 02:36:06,321
What's my name?
...how to talk.

1590
02:36:06,621 --> 02:36:08,735
I'm Daisy.

1591
02:36:08,943 --> 02:36:11,443
Can you say Daisy?

1592
02:36:12,485 --> 02:36:17,860
In 2002, they put up a new
clock in that train station.

1593
02:36:24,568 --> 02:36:28,610
And in the spring of 2003,

1594
02:36:32,443 --> 02:36:35,235
he looked at me,

1595
02:36:36,743 --> 02:36:41,622
and I knew that
he knew who I was.

1596
02:36:45,452 --> 02:36:51,276
And then he closed his eyes
as if he would go to sleep.

1597
02:37:23,693 --> 02:37:26,286
I wish I had known him.

1598
02:37:26,575 --> 02:37:28,779
Now you do.

1599
02:37:32,276 --> 02:37:36,526
Mom, I think I should go
see what's going on.

1600
02:37:43,235 --> 02:37:46,110
Goodnight, Benjamin.

1601
02:38:15,401 --> 02:38:19,030
Some people are born
to sit by a river.

1602
02:38:19,651 --> 02:38:22,610
Some get struck by lightning.

1603
02:38:23,443 --> 02:38:26,360
Some have an ear for music.

1604
02:38:27,193 --> 02:38:29,576
Some are artists.

1605
02:38:30,243 --> 02:38:32,287
Some swim.

1606
02:38:32,860 --> 02:38:35,485
Some know buttons.

1607
02:38:36,443 --> 02:38:40,902
Some know Shakespeare.
Some are mothers.

1608
02:38:42,776 --> 02:38:46,247
And some people... dance.

